==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equilibrate
<hw>E`qui*li"brate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Equilibrated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Equilibrating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>aequilibratus</ets> in
equilibrium; <ets>aequus</ets> equal + <ets>libra</ets> balance. See
<er>Equilibrium</er>.]</ety> <def>To balance two scales, sides, or ends;
to keep even with equal weight on each side; to keep in equipoise.</def>
<rj><au>H. Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

